    {
      "index": 5,
      "title": "Overhead Triceps Extension (Cable)",
      "notes": "Sets: 3 Working Sets (Cut from 4 sets).\n\nTarget: 8-12 reps @ RPE 10.\n\nRest: 2m 0s\n\nYour elbows are the hinge, they don't move at all. Only your forearms move. If your elbows are drifting or dropping during the rep, you're using shoulder to compensate.\n\nSetup (seated version removes the instability):\n- Sit on a bench facing away from the cable stack\n- Pull the rope/handle over your head, elbows pointing to the ceiling\n- Upper arms stay vertical, close to your head \u2014 don't let them drift forward or flare out\n- Extend forearms up until straight, squeeze, then controlled 3s down\n- The bench gives you a fixed reference so elbow height becomes automatic\n",
